When buying crypto in a bear/sideways market, I aim to get the "best avg price" n not the "lowest price". There is NO way anyone can CONSISTENTLY predict tops n bottoms. Knowing tops and bottoms does NOT make u a trader. Knowing how to SIZE ur bets CORRECTLY makes u a trader.

Don't let the doom n gloom folks, broke ass folks, non traders, n conspiracy theory idiots prevent u from BUYING during this sideways market. Do NOT buy everything all at once. SLOWLY buy in small chunks. This reduces emotional stress in case price falls.

Just a reminder to everyone that crypto is going sideways & a good time to be BUYING. If I had $100 to put into crypto, I'd by buying $1-5 at a time each wk, If I had $1K, I'd be buying $10-50, $100-$500 if I had $10K, etc. This process trains u to slowly buy n average in.

Stats for new crypto traders... a CONSISTENTLY PROFITABLE stock/forex TREND trader makes $ on roughly 25-34% of their trades. This means they are wrong n lose $ on 2/3 of their trades. They take small losses when they're WRONG n let profits run the small % of time they're RIGHT.

Consistently UNPROFITABLE traders focus on being RIGHT in crypto so they can brag about being right.  Consistently PROFITABLE traders focus on making money n ask themselves, "How can I build a trading system where I can be WRONG the majority of the time and still be PROFITABLE?"
